      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pervasive use of \"fake news\" has ironically fueled a digital echo chamber where users trust only sources that confirm their pre-existing biases. Instead of acting as a banner to discard falsehoods, the term often becomes a weapon used to dismiss liberal media coverage as inherently unreliable, deepening the cultural divide over what constitutes real information. This dynamic accelerates misinformation because people engage more aggressively with content they see labeled as fake, rather than seeking verification from impartial journalists. Ultimately, the language has shifted our political diet from a common marketplace to a fragmented series of walled gardens where objective facts often lose out to emotional validation.",
