      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term functions primarily as a political slogan to label mainstream outlets biased against wealthier voters, rather than reflecting an actual epidemic of factual errors within those organizations. While erratic news cycles exist, reputable liberal media still adheres to journalistic ethics far more than it does to partisan talking points on either side. The problem isn't low standards at traditional publications but rather the sheer volume of paid troll farms exploiting the slogan for agenda-setting. Ultimately, using \"fake news\" has amounted to elitist character assassination against the press corps that is actually doing the most rigorous lifting.",
