      "content": "wait so u're saying the accusations of fake news are basically just character assassination? that seems like a pretty strong take. aren't there also people who argue that mainstream media has its own baked-in biases that make it \"fake\" from their perspective? how do you distinguish between legitimate criticism of media bias and just someone using the term as a political weapon?",
